            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>In nomine Domini. Consta me <persName key="#Deacons #Abbots #Monks"
                            ref="#people/1554">Andreas</persName> gratja Dei <rs key="#Deacons"
                            >diac(onus)</rs> et <rs key="#Monks">monahus</rs> atque <rs
                            key="#Abbots">abb(as)</rs> regule <rs key="#Monasteries"
                            >mon(asterii)</rs>
                        <orgName
                            key="#Fundi #Landed_possessions #Rent_in_money #Monasteries #Deacons #Abbots #Monks"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/1487">Sancti Apolenaris qui vocatur
                            Novo</orgName> accepissem et accepi at vobis <persName><name
                                ref="Apollinaris">Apolenaris</name></persName> filio quondam
                                <persName><name ref="Iohannes">Ioh(anni)s</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Rent_in_money">pensionem</rs> pro tres <rs
                            key="#Landed_possessions">untjas</rs> in int(egro) qui est posita in <rs
                            key="#Fundi">fundum</rs> qui vocatur <geogName
                            key="#Fundi #Landed_possessions #Rent_in_money" ref="#estates/2421"
                                ><placeName key="#Fundi #Landed_possessions #Rent_in_money"
                                >Colopedio</placeName></geogName> cum omnibus sibi pertinentibus,
                        territorio <geogName key="#Fundi #Fines" ref="#estates/2422"><placeName
                                key="#Fundi #Fines" ref="#places/3515"
                            >Liv(iense)</placeName></geogName>, <rs key="#Plebs">pl(ebe)</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Plebs" ref="#juridical_persons/1488">Sancte
                            Reparate</orgName>, quas per <rs key="#Libellus/precaria/emphyteusis"
                            >enfiteusin</rs> tenere viso estis at iure suprascripti mon(asterii)
                        nostri, pro indicionibus transactus usque in ista press(ente) tertja et per
                        unaquaque ind(itjone) den(arii) quinque tantum. Unde pro munimine vestro
                        fetjt vobis unc deaccepto in mense martjo, ind(itjone) suprascripta tertja,
                            <placeName ref="#places/594">Ra[venne]</placeName>. Andrea et abba
                        S(an)c(t)i Apolinaris in oc diaccepto s(ub)s(cripsi).</ab>
                </div>
